Class PickupManagerImpl

    PickupManager

    @ApplicationScoped
 @PickupManagerDB
public class PickupManagerImpl
extends GenericManagerImpl
implements PickupManager
    Pickup pLace manager class.

    This class is used to manage pickup places according to the business logic. It should be used by the controllers to handle pickup places like adding, deleting and so. The access of one of data access object method by the controllers is strictly forbidden.

    See Also:
    add(Item, String, String, String), find(Item), update(PickupPlace, HashMap), delete(PickupPlace)

      • add

        public PickupPlace add(Item item,
                       java.lang.String street,
                       java.lang.String zipCode,
                       java.lang.String city)
                throws ModelException
        Create a pickup place.

        This method create a pickup place and save it into the database. The newly created pickup place is attached to the supplied item after successfully saved. Creating a pickup place for an item not in waiting or active state will result in an exception generated.

        Specified by:
        add in interface PickupManager
        Parameters:
        item - Item to add the pickup place to
        street - Street where to pick up the item.
        zipCode - Zip code where to pick up the item.
        city - City to pick up the item.
        Returns:
        The newly created pickup place.
        Throws:
        ModelException - In case of problem.

      • find

        public PickupPlace find(@NotNull
                        @NotNull Item item)
                 throws ModelException
        Find the pickup place that belong to an item.

        This method find the pickup place related to the item supplied in parameter. If no pickup place is found, that means the item should be picked up at the seller address.

        Specified by:
        find in interface PickupManager
        Parameters:
        item - Item for which finding the pickup place.
        Returns:
        Found pickup place.
        Throws:
        ModelException - In case of problem or if nothing is found.

        Update pickup place properties.

        This method update the properties of the supplied pickup place. Each property new value should be supplied as a pair of key/value, a key representing the exact name of the pickup place property, including case. If a key as an undefined property name, an exception is generated.

      • delete

        public void delete(@NotNull
                   @NotNull PickupPlace pickupPlace)
            throws ModelException
        Delete a pickup place.

        This method delete a pickup place from the database. Only items that are in waiting or active state can have their pickup place deleted. Once the pickup place is deleted, his previously attached item is updated too.

        Specified by:
        delete in interface PickupManager
        Parameters:
